id: pm-3cbk
title: Keep large modules maintainable via barrel re-export splits + explicit uncovered allowlist
description: "Decisions taken while completing pm-mbdu (file splits) and pm-zwl7 (extension error surfacing): (1) BARREL RE-EXPORT pattern: extract cohesive leaf clusters from oversized files into sibling modules, then re-export from the original so NO consumer import site changes; the original imports FROM the new modules to avoid cycles. (2) COVERAGE MODEL: new split modules are deliberately NOT added to vitest.config.ts coverage 'include' (so they inherit their parent's ungated status); they MUST instead be registered in the explicit uncovered allowlist governance test in tests/integration/release-readiness-runtime.spec.ts ('keeps vitest coverage include list aligned with src ts modules'). The static-quality-gate alone does NOT catch a missing allowlist entry — only the full coverage gate does. (3) EXTENSION ERROR SURFACING: surface a handler's failure cause via a dedicated errorMessage field on CommandHandlerResult (NOT inside the warnings array) so the telemetry warning code stays generic while the human cause reaches stderr; telemetry's existing sanitizeString(captureLevel) redacts paths from outcome.error. (4) CHANGELOG is fully auto-generated by the pm-changelog package from CLOSED items — never hand-edit CHANGELOG.md; close items (with accurate type/tags so classifyItem routes them) then run 'pnpm changelog:pm' to regenerate."
type: Decision
status: open
priority: 2
tags[1]: agent-ux
